:::summary
Greek mythology is the body of stories concerning the gods, heroes, cosmology, and religious practices of ancient Greece. These myths were not merely entertainment but formed the religious, moral, and cultural framework of Greek civilization, explaining the origins of the world, the nature of divine beings, and the proper relationship between gods and mortals. Through Homer, Hesiod, the tragedians, and the visual arts, Greek mythology became the single greatest influence on Western literature, art, and imagination.
:::

